We will later analyze a specific model, and see that this class of theories opens up new possibilities for supersymmetry model building.

First, let us illustrate a few other possibilities. Consider a specific case: the SU (7) model with an antisymmetric tensor and three _7's. Now reduce the gauge group to SU (5)\Theta SU (2)\Theta U (1), with the U (1) generator taken to be ~T = diag(2; 2; 2; 2; 2; \Gamma 5; \Gamma 5). The fields decompose as

