Note the structure of the theory at this level. Squarks are the most massive scalar fields, by roughly a factor of three compared to slepton and Higgs doublets. Slepton

14

singlets are the lightest scalar fields, by still another factor of order three. Gluinos have masses comparable to squarks, while the Majorana component of the wino mass matrix is comparable to that of the doublets. Note also that the strict degeneracy of squarks and of sleptons of the same gauge quantum numbers is only broken by effects of order quark or lepton Yukawa couplings. We will see that experimental constraints give masses for squarks and gluinos in the 200 \Gamma 300 GeV range. This means that \Lambda , 10 T eV . This is the scale of X physics. The scale of the hidden sector SU (6) \Theta U (1) physics is larger by a factor of order (4ss)

