3 TeV for coupling constants of order one. Note that

this corresponds to a rather large value of the gravitino mass (of order 1 keV), which is marginally consistent with the upper bounds on the energy of the universe [23]. If the gravitino mass comes out too large, a period of late inflation might solve this and other problems (see x6).

We are particularly interested in the potential for the Higgs field. In the next section, we will explain how a _HU HD term in the superpotential can be naturally generated in this framework. Here we note, first, that a coupling in the superpotential:

