A.2. A Nonrenormalizable SU (N ) \Theta Sp(M ) Generalization of the SU (3) \Theta SU (2) Model

A rather clumsy generalization of the SU (3)\Theta SU (2) model has gauge group SU (N )\Theta Sp(M ), N odd, M even, and N ? M . Again this model has an R symmetry and SU (N ) dynamically generates a superpotential, so supersymmetry is broken if there are no flat directions. The matter fields are

Q , (N; M ); _Qi , ( _N ; 1); M , (1; M ) ; (A.4) where i = 1; :::; M is a flavor index. The superpotential is

